\bibitem{birkhoff1930formal}
George~D. Birkhoff.
\newblock Formal theory of irregular linear difference equations.
\newblock {\em Acta Mathematica}, 54:205--246, 1930.
\newblock Section~2 (formal canonical form) establishes uniformly that any $n
  \times n$ linear system at an irregular singular point of rank $q$ admits a
  formal series solution carrying the standard $z$-power factor; Section~3
  records the converse uniqueness modulo formal-equivalence. The
  Borel-summability content is treated in the companion Birkhoff--Trjitzinsky
  1933 paper, not in \S\S2--3 of this 1930 paper (cf.\ Q20A dispatch~3
  spec-error finding).

