\bibitem{wasow1965asymptotic}
Wolfgang Wasow.
\newblock {\em Asymptotic Expansions for Ordinary Differential Equations}.
\newblock Pure and Applied Mathematics, Vol.~XIV. Interscience Publishers, John
  Wiley \& Sons (Reprint: Dover, 1987), 1965.
\newblock Chapter IV \S\S10--15 (distinct-eigenvalue case) and Chapter V
  \S\S16--19 (general / multiple-eigenvalue case) carry the Main Asymptotic
  Existence Theorem uniformly in the irregular-singularity rank. Theorem~12.1
  (\S12, distinct case): for nonnegative integer rank, the corresponding linear
  system has a fundamental matrix solution analytic in any sector of central
  angle bounded by a $1/(\mathrm{rank}+1)$ fraction of $\pi$, asymptotic to the
  formal solution. Theorem~19.1 (\S19.5, general case): same conclusion for any
  holomorphic coefficient matrix, with formal solution carrying a Puiseux
  gauge. Equation~(19.3) is the gauge form encoding the Borel-singularity
  radius at the rank-$q$ irregular singular point.

